cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with improving the accuracy of OCR by enhancing the quality of low-resolution document images. This involves the use of deep learning techniques and loss functions to preserve original patterns and enhance the edges of characters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models and optimization techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
